# SECTION 5: KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

---

## 5.1 Part A Questions (3 Marks Each)

> **[KTU University Exam – May 2024, Model Question]**

### **Q1. Differentiate between `req.params` and `req.query` in Express.js with suitable examples.** `[3 Marks]`

**Model Answer:**

| Feature | `req.params` | `req.query` |
|---|---|---|
| **Source** | URL path segments (named placeholders) | URL query string (after `?`) |
| **Syntax** | Defined with `:` prefix in route | Key-value pairs separated by `&` |
| **Example URL** | `/users/:id` matched by `/users/101` | `/search?q=express&page=2` |
| **Access** | `req.params.id` → `"101"` | `req.query.q` → `"express"`, `req.query.page` → `"2"` |
| **Data Type** | String (must be parsed manually if numeric) | String (must be parsed manually) |
| **Use Case** | Identifying a specific resource | Filtering, sorting, pagination, search |

**Example Route:**

```javascript
// req.params
app.get('/users/:id', (req, res) => {
  res.send(`User ID: ${req.params.id}`);
});

// req.query
app.get('/search', (req, res) => {
  res.send(`Query: ${req.query.q}, Page: ${req.query.page}`);
});
```

---

> **[KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]**

### **Q2. What is middleware in Express.js? List any three built-in middleware functions.** `[3 Marks]`

**Model Answer:**

**Middleware** is a function that has access to the request object (`req`), response object (`res`), and the next middleware function in the application's request-response cycle. It can execute code, modify `req`/`res`, end the request, or call `next()` to pass control to the next middleware.

**Three Built-in Middleware Functions:**

1. **`express.json()`** — Parses incoming requests with JSON payloads and exposes the result on `req.body`.
2. **`express.urlencoded({ extended: true })`** — Parses URL-encoded form data (e.g., from HTML forms).
3. **`express.static(root)`** — Serves static files (images, CSS, JS) from the specified root directory.

