#### Model Solution for Q.B(a):

**Middleware Definition:**

A **middleware function** in Express.js is a function that executes during the lifecycle of an HTTP request. It has access to three objects: `req` (request), `res` (response), and `next` (callback to invoke the next middleware). The signature is:

$$
\text{Middleware}(req, res, next) \rightarrow \text{Void}
$$

Middleware can:
- Execute any code
- Make changes to `req` and `res` objects
- End the request-response cycle by calling `res.send()` / `res.json()`
- Pass control to the next middleware via `next()`

**Types of Middleware:**

| Type | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| **Application-Level** | Bound to the `app` object via `app.use()` or `app.METHOD()`. Executes for all (or filtered) routes. | `app.use((req,res,next) => { console.log(req.url); next(); });` |
| **Router-Level** | Bound to an `express.Router()` instance. Works exactly like application-level but is scoped to the router. | `router.use(authMiddleware);` |
| **Error-Handling** | Recognized by its **four-argument signature** `(err, req, res, next)`. Triggered when `next(err)` is called. | `app.use((err, req, res, next) => { res.status(500).send(err.message); });` |
| **Built-in** | Shipped with Express, no installation required. | `express.json()`, `express.static()`, `express.urlencoded()` |
| **Third-Party** | Installed via npm and integrated with `app.use()`. | `morgan` (logging), `cors` (Cross-Origin), `helmet` (security), `cookie-parser` |

**Code Examples:**

```javascript
// 1. Application-level
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log(`${req.method} ${req.url} at ${new Date()}`);
  next();
});

// 2. Router-level
const router = express.Router();
router.use((req, res, next) => { /* scoped logic */ next(); });

// 3. Error-handling (4 args!)
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack);
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Server Error' });
});

// 4. Built-in
app.use(express.json());
app.use(express.static('public'));

// 5. Third-party (npm install morgan cors helmet)
const morgan = require('morgan');
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(morgan('dev'));
app.use(cors());
```

