## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mistakes That Cost Marks in KTU Exams:**
>
> 1. **Forgetting to call `next()` in middleware** — Causes the request to hang indefinitely, leading to client-side timeouts. *(−2 marks)*
> 2. **Using `res.send()` followed by `res.json()`** — Throws a runtime error: *"Cannot set headers after they are sent to the client"*. Always `return` after sending. *(−2 marks)*
> 3. **Confusing `req.params` and `req.query`** — Examiners specifically test this. Remember: **colon-prefixed path segments** → params; **after `?`** → query. *(−3 marks if swapped)*
> 4. **Not registering `express.json()` middleware** — `req.body` will be `undefined` in POST handlers, leading to validation logic failures. *(−2 marks)*
> 5. **Using 3-argument signature for error middleware** — Express only recognizes error middleware by its **4-argument** signature `(err, req, res, next)`. A 3-arg function will NOT catch errors. *(−3 marks)*
> 6. **Returning the response object without using `res.status()`** — Defaults to 200, but explicit status codes are mandatory in RESTful API design. *(−1 mark per occurrence)*

