## PART A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Q1. **[KTU University Exam — Dec 2023]**
**Define Mongoose. What is the difference between an ODM and an ORM?**

**Model Answer:**
Mongoose is an **Object Data Modeling (ODM)** library for **MongoDB** and **Node.js** that provides a schema-based solution to model application data, including built-in type casting, validation, query building, and business logic hooks (middleware).

**ODM vs ORM:**
| Aspect | ODM (Mongoose) | ORM (Sequelize/Prisma) |
|---|---|---|
| Database Type | NoSQL (Document) | SQL (Relational) |
| Maps To | Documents / Collections | Rows / Tables |
| Schema | Enforced by library | Enforced by DB |
| Example | Mongoose for MongoDB | Sequelize for PostgreSQL |

