# 3. Step-by-Step Implementation & Analytical Matrix

Below is an **exhaustive, copy-pasteable, fully-commented** Express implementation covering every concept KTU 2024 examiners tend to test: single upload, array upload, file filtering, size limits, and serving the uploaded image statically.

## 3.1 Project Bootstrap

```bash
mkdir express-upload-demo
cd express-upload-demo
npm init -y
npm install express multer
```

The package.json should declare `"type": "commonjs"` (or use ES Modules with `"type": "module"`).

## 3.2 Server Code – Annotated Line by Line

```javascript
// server.js
const express  = require('express');
const multer   = require('multer');
const path     = require('path');
const fs       = require('fs');

const app  = express();
const PORT = 3000;

// --- 3.2.1 Ensure uploads directory exists ---------------------------
const uploadDir = path.join(__dirname, 'uploads');
if (!fs.existsSync(uploadDir)) fs.mkdirSync(uploadDir, { recursive: true });

// --- 3.2.2 Disk storage configuration --------------------------------
const storage = multer.diskStorage({
  destination: (req, file, cb) => {
    cb(null, uploadDir);              // folder to store
  },
  filename: (req, file, cb) => {
    const uniqueSuffix = Date.now() + '-' + Math.round(Math.random() * 1e9);
    const ext          = path.extname(file.originalname);   // .png
    cb(null, `${file.fieldname}-${uniqueSuffix}${ext}`);   // avatar-1716…png
  }
});

// --- 3.2.3 File filter – only allow images ---------------------------
const ALLOWED = new Set(['image/jpeg', 'image/png', 'image/gif', 'image/webp']);
const fileFilter = (req, file, cb) => {
  if (ALLOWED.has(file.mimetype)) cb(null, true);
  else cb(new Error('Only image files (jpg/png/gif/webp) are allowed!'), false);
};

// --- 3.2.4 Multer instance with limits -------------------------------
const upload = multer({
  storage,
  fileFilter,
  limits: { fileSize: 5 * 1024 * 1024 }  // 5 MB
});

// --- 3.2.5 Routes ----------------------------------------------------

// SINGLE FILE – field name must be "avatar"
app.post('/upload/single', upload.single('avatar'), (req, res) => {
  if (!req.file) return res.status(400).json({ error: 'No file received' });
  res.status(200).json({
    message : 'Single image uploaded',
    file    : {
      filename   : req.file.filename,
      size       : req.file.size,
      mimetype   : req.file.mimetype,
      url        : `/static/${req.file.filename}`
    }
  });
});

// MULTIPLE FILES – up to 5 under field "photos"
app.post('/upload/multiple', upload.array('photos', 5), (req, res) => {
  const files = req.files.map(f => ({
    filename : f.filename,
    size     : f.size
  }));
  res.status(200).json({ message: 'Images uploaded', count: files.length, files });
});

// MIXED FIELDS – one avatar + up to 3 gallery images
app.post(
  '/upload/mixed',
  upload.fields([
    { name: 'avatar',  maxCount: 1 },
    { name: 'gallery', maxCount: 3 }
  ]),
  (req, res) => {
    res.status(200).json({
      avatar  : req.files['avatar']  ? req.files['avatar'][0].filename  : null,
      gallery : (req.files['gallery'] || []).map(f => f.filename)
    });
  }
);

// --- 3.2.6 Serve uploaded files statically ---------------------------
app.use('/static', express.static(uploadDir));

// --- 3.2.7 Global error handler (Multer errors) ----------------------
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  if (err instanceof multer.MulterError) {
    return res.status(400).json({ multerError: err.code, message: err.message });
  }
  if (err) return res.status(415).json({ error: err.message });
  next();
});

app.listen(PORT, () =>
  console.log(`Server running on http://localhost:${PORT}`)
);
```

## 3.3 Mathematical View of the Filename Function

The unique-suffix generator can be expressed as:

$$
\text{filename} \;=\; \text{fieldname} \;+\; \text{'-'} \;+\; f(t,\, r)
$$

where

$$
f(t, r) = t \cdot 10^{3} \;+\; \lfloor r \cdot 10^{9} \rceil
$$

with $t$ = `Date.now()` (ms since epoch) and $r$ = pseudo-random real in $[0,1)$.

For example, at $t = 1716382919234$ and $r = 0.473928$:

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{suffix} &= 1716382919234000 + 473928000 \\
              &= 1716382843162000 \\
\text{filename} &= \texttt{"avatar-1716382843162000.png"}
\end{aligned}
$$

The collision probability for two concurrent uploads follows the **birthday-bound approximation**:

$$
P(\text{collision}) \;\approx\; 1 - e^{-n^{2} \,/\, (2M)}
$$

with $n$ = simultaneous uploads and $M = 10^{9}$. For $n = 1000$, $P \approx 0.0005$, i.e. effectively zero – satisfying KTU's expectation of "no two files share a name".

## 3.4 Analytical Matrix – Common Pitfalls vs. Correct Patterns

| # | Symptom | Root Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `req.file` is `undefined` | Form's `enctype` missing OR field name mismatch | Use `enctype="multipart/form-data"` and ensure `name` matches the Multer call |
| 2 | `LIMIT_UNEXPECTED_FILE` | Frontend sends different field name | Match names: `upload.single('avatar')` ↔ `name="avatar"` |
| 3 | Server crashes on large image | No `limits.fileSize` set | Add `limits: { fileSize: 5 * 1024 * 1024 }` |
| 4 | `error: file too large` even for small images | Browser sends wrong MIME (e.g. `application/octet-stream`) | Use `fileFilter` that inspects *both* `mimetype` and `path.extname()` |
| 5 | Uploaded file has spaces/special chars | No sanitization of `file.originalname` | Replace with the generated `uniqueSuffix` filename (as shown) |

