# 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

## Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Q1. **[KTU University Exam – May 2024]**
**List the two methods by which uploaded images can be stored in a database. State one advantage and one disadvantage of each.**

**Model Answer:**
Two methods:
1. **BLOB Storage** – Image binary data stored in a `BLOB`/`LONGBLOB` column.
   - *Advantage:* Atomic with row data; one `mysqldump` captures everything.
   - *Disadvantage:* Bloats DB; slower retrieval for large media.
2. **File-Path Storage** – Image saved in a server folder, only the relative path stored as `VARCHAR`.
   - *Advantage:* Web server serves files directly; CDN-friendly.
   - *Disadvantage:* Backup becomes a two-step process (DB + folder).

### Q2. **[KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]**
**Why is `enctype="multipart/form-data"` mandatory in an image upload form? What happens if it is omitted?**

**Model Answer:**
`enctype="multipart/form-data"` instructs the browser to encode the form body as **MIME multipart**, allowing binary file bytes to traverse HTTP without URL-encoding. If omitted, the default `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` converts bytes into percent-encoded text, **corrupting the binary stream**. PHP's `$_FILES` array will be empty and `move_uploaded_file()` will fail.

