# 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

## 5.1 Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Q1. `[KTU University Exam — Dec 2023]`
**Differentiate between stateful and stateless logout mechanisms. Which is more secure against stolen tokens and why?**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

| Aspect | Stateful Logout | Stateless Logout (JWT) |
|---|---|---|
| Server storage | Session record in DB/store | No storage by default |
| Revocation method | `req.session.destroy()` | Blacklist `jti` in Redis |
| Revocation speed | Instant | Instant (after blacklist check) |
| Scalability | Limited by store | Higher (no store lookup on every request) |

**Security verdict (1 mark):** Stateless logout is **more secure against stolen tokens only when combined with a blacklist**; without one, a stolen JWT remains valid till natural expiry, making stateless logout weaker in the naive implementation.

### Q2. `[KTU University Exam — May 2024]`
**List any three security attributes that MUST be set on the session cookie during logout handling.**

**Model Answer (3 marks — 1 mark each):**
1. **`HttpOnly`** — Prevents JavaScript from reading the cookie, mitigating XSS-based session theft.
2. **`Secure`** — Ensures the cookie is transmitted only over HTTPS, preventing network sniffing.
3. **`SameSite=Lax` (or Strict)** — Blocks the cookie from being sent on cross-site requests, mitigating CSRF-driven forced logout.

