## 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Rapid Revision Checklist — Memory Game**

- ⭐ **Three card states:** HIDDEN, FLIPPED, MATCHED — track via CSS classes (`.flipped`, `.matched`).
- ⭐ **Fisher–Yates Shuffle:** $O(n)$ time, $O(1)$ space, **uniformly random**. Avoid `sort(() => Math.random() - 0.5)`.
- ⭐ **Always duplicate the symbols array** to create pairs: `[...symbols, ...symbols]`.
- ⭐ **The `boardLocked` boolean** is mandatory to prevent rapid clicks during the mismatch delay.
- ⭐ **`setTimeout` delay** is typically **1000 ms** — long enough for the player to memorize positions.
- ⭐ **Use `dataset.value`** to store each card's symbol — avoids parsing DOM text content.
- ⭐ **CSS 3D flip:** `transform: rotateY(180deg)` + `backface-visibility: hidden` on both faces.
- ⭐ **Win condition:** `matchedCount === cardsArray.length / 2`.
- ⭐ **Restart must:** re-shuffle, reset all counters (`moves`, `score`, `matched`), and re-render the DOM.
- ⭐ **Move counter** increments once per *pair of flips*, not per single card flip.
- ⭐ **Score formula (standard):** `+10` per match; can be extended to include time/move penalties.
- ⭐ **Time complexity of entire game:** $O(n)$ initialization, $O(1)$ per click.
- ⭐ **Event delegation tip:** In larger boards, attach **one listener** to the board and use `event.target` — saves memory.

