## 5.1 Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### **Q1. [KTU University Exam – May 2024]**
**Explain the role of `useEffect` hook in a React Movie App. How does its dependency array affect API call behavior?**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

`useEffect` is a React Hook that performs **side-effects** in function components — such as fetching data from an API, subscribing to events, or manually updating the DOM. In a Movie App, `useEffect` is used to call TMDB endpoints when a component mounts or when a search query changes.

- **Empty dependency array `[]`** → effect runs **once** on mount (e.g., loading popular movies on the home page).
- **Array with values `[query]`** → effect runs on mount **and** whenever `query` changes (e.g., search functionality).
- **No array** → effect runs on **every render**, which is usually a performance anti-pattern.

The cleanup function (returned from `useEffect`) is used to abort in-flight requests via `AbortController`, preventing memory leaks.

*(1 mark for definition, 1 mark for dependency array explanation, 1 mark for cleanup/abort use case.)*

### **Q2. [KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]**
**What is the significance of the TMDB image base URL `https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/` in a Movie App? List any two size flags.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

TMDB returns **only relative poster paths** (e.g., `/abc123.jpg`) in its JSON responses. To display the actual image, the developer must **concatenate** the base URL with a size flag and the relative path:

$$ \text{Full Image URL} = \texttt{https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/} + \text{size\_flag} + \text{poster\_path} $$

**Two common size flags:**
1. `w185` — small thumbnail (~185 px wide), used in mobile cards.
2. `w500` — medium poster (~500 px wide), used in detail pages.
3. `original` — full resolution, used for hero banners.

*(1 mark for URL concatenation logic, 1 mark each for the two size flags with use-case.)*

