## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Pitfalls That Cost Marks in Module 7 — Movie App Questions:**
> 1. **Forgetting API authentication header** — TMDB requires `Authorization: Bearer <v4_token>`. A missing header will cause a 401 in the demo; examiners deduct **2 marks**.
> 2. **Not concatenating the image base URL** — Writing `<img src={movie.poster_path} />` shows broken images. Always use `${IMG_BASE}${poster_path}`. **−2 marks**.
> 3. **Missing `key` prop in lists** — React will throw a console warning and examiners consider this a violation of best practices. **−1 mark**.
> 4. **Calling setState after unmount** — Forgetting the `cancelled` flag or `AbortController` cleanup in `useEffect` leads to memory-leak warnings. **−1 mark**.
> 5. **Not handling loading and error states** — A real app must show a spinner and an error message. UI that hangs on a blank screen loses **1–2 marks**.
> 6. **Prop drilling favorites instead of using Context** — Examiners specifically test for Context API awareness in the 2024 scheme. **−2 marks**.

