> **Quick-Fire Revision Points — Movie App (Module 7)**

- [ ] A Movie App is an **SPA** consuming the **TMDB REST API** via Axios.
- [ ] Project setup uses **Vite + React 18+**, dependencies: `axios`, `react-router-dom`.
- [ ] **Layered architecture**: Presentation (components/pages) → Logic (hooks) → Service (api.js) → External (TMDB).
- [ ] **Core components**: `Navbar`, `MovieList`, `MovieCard`, `MovieDetail`, `Favorites`, `Spinner`, `Footer`.
- [ ] **Core hooks**: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useContext`, `useParams`, plus custom `useFetchMovies`, `useDebounce`, `useLocalStorage`.
- [ ] **TMDB image base URL** is `https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/`; append size flag + `poster_path`.
- [ ] **Bearer Token (v4)** is passed via `Authorization` header in Axios instance.
- [ ] **Debounce search** at **400 ms** to avoid hammering the API.
- [ ] **`Promise.all`** for parallel API calls reduces latency by ~50%.
- [ ] **`AbortController`** in `useEffect` cleanup cancels in-flight requests on unmount.
- [ ] **Context API** is the global state manager for `favorites`; avoids prop drilling.
- [ ] **`localStorage` key** is `movie_favorites`; serialize with `JSON.stringify`, hydrate with `JSON.parse`.
- [ ] **`React Router`** uses `<BrowserRouter>`, `<Routes>`, `<Route>`, `<Link>`, and `useParams()` for dynamic `/movie/:id`.
- [ ] **Conditional rendering** pattern: `{loading ? <Spinner/> : <MovieList movies={data}/>}`.
- [ ] **`e.preventDefault()` + `e.stopPropagation()`** on nested buttons inside `<Link>` to prevent unwanted navigation.
- [ ] **Lazy loading** images with `loading="lazy"` improves **LCP** (Largest Contentful Paint).
- [ ] **Responsive grid**: `grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr))`.
- [ ] **Error boundary pattern**: `try / catch / finally` ensures `loading=false` even on failure.
- [ ] **Key prop** in mapped lists: `movies.map(m => <MovieCard key={m.id} movie={m} />)`.
- [ ] **Toggle operation** is set-theoretic: $F_{n+1} = F_n \oplus \{m\}$.
- [ ] **Routing paths**: `/` (Home), `/movie/:id` (Detail), `/favorites` (Favorites), `*` (NotFound).
- [ ] **Environment variable** for API key: stored in `.env` as `VITE_TMDB_TOKEN` (Vite convention) or `REACT_APP_TMDB_TOKEN` (CRA convention).

