### **Q1. [KTU University Exam – June 2024, Model Question]**
**Define RESTful API. List the four main HTTP methods used in a Library App and state the CRUD operation each performs.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

**REST (Representational State Transfer)** is an architectural style for designing networked applications where every URL represents a *resource* and HTTP verbs represent *actions* on that resource. It is **stateless**, meaning the server stores no client session — every request must carry all context (typically a JWT).

The four main HTTP methods mapped to CRUD are:

| HTTP Method | CRUD Operation | Example Endpoint |
|---|---|---|
| `POST` | **C**reate | `POST /api/books` |
| `GET` | **R**ead | `GET /api/books` |
| `PUT` | **U**pdate | `PUT /api/books/:id` |
| `DELETE` | **D**elete | `DELETE /api/books/:id` |

> *Marking guide: 1 mark for REST definition, 1 mark for listing, 1 mark for correct mapping.*

