> [!WARNING]
> ## ⚠️ KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning — Common Pitfalls
> 
> **Where students lose marks in Library App questions:**
> 
> 1. **❌ Forgetting `await` keywords** — `Book.findById(id)` returns a **Promise**. Without `await`, you get a Promise object, not the document. This is the **#1 mistake** in 14-mark code questions.
> 
> 2. **❌ Wrong status code for CREATE** — `POST` should return **201 Created**, not 200. Examiners deduct 1 mark for this.
> 
> 3. **❌ Storing plain-text passwords** — Always use `bcrypt.hash()` before saving. Writing `password: req.body.password` in the User schema is a **security blunder** worth losing 2 marks.
> 
> 4. **❌ Not calling `next()` in middleware** — If middleware neither responds nor calls `next()`, the request hangs and the server eventually times out. Examiners check for this.
> 
> 5. **❌ Confusing `PUT` vs `PATCH`** — `PUT` replaces the *entire* resource; `PATCH` does a partial update. KTU expects `PUT` for full updates.
> 
> 6. **❌ Missing `runValidators: true` in `findByIdAndUpdate`** — Without it, schema validations are bypassed on updates, letting bad data slip in. Examiners **will** deduct marks.
> 
> 7. **❌ Returning the full `req.body` in responses** — This can leak sensitive fields like passwords. Always select specific fields to return.

